         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">19/8/61 ¶ My dear Müller ¶  ¶ Many thanks for the book list. ¶  ¶ I quite agree with yr. suggestion and will reserve £25 for payment to Mr. Oldfield ¶  for collections in  ¶ Insects ¶   ¶ small mammal...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.08.19b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick McCoy</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Director’s letterbooks, MVS 2/1 1, p. 375, Melbourne Museum.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">19/8/61</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Müller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for the book list.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I quite agree with yr. suggestion and will reserve £25 for payment to Mr. Oldfield<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M had proposed that Augustus Oldfield accompany the Burke and Wills relief expedition to the Gulf of Carpentaria as botanical collector; see M to R. Heales, 18 July 1861. In the event, Oldfield did not go, his place being taken by Diedrich Henne. The expedition had departed, however, on 4 August, so McCoy would have known that Oldfield had not gone with it. He and M must therefore have been planning some other collecting expedition for Oldfield.</p>
               </note> for collections in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Insects</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">small mammals</hi>
               </seg> and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Land &amp; freshwater Shells</hi>
               </seg> particularly or birds for the Nat. Mus.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">National Museum.</p>
               </note> for wh. (as well as our set as you mention of his plant series) the Museum will be responsible if you wd. have the kindness to communicate the order.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Very &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>F. McC.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr. F. Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
